This article is a statement by the President on NASA Day of Remembrance. The President reflects on the sacrifices made by astronauts in the history of NASA and acknowledges the tragic loss of the Apollo 1 crew, the space shuttle Challenger crew, and the space shuttle Columbia crew. The President emphasizes the importance of NASA's new 21st Century course, which aims to foster new industries, create jobs, pioneer technology innovation, and inspire a new generation of explorers through education. The President calls on everyone to honor the memory of these brave astronauts by dedicating themselves to a better future.